comments[15]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-03-31T21:28:33.277Z",codex-agent,Task created for markdown-default calendar output handling.
  "2026-03-31T21:45:12.525Z",codex-agent,Added calendar-specific markdown default rendering with explicit --format and --json override precedence checks.
  "2026-03-31T21:45:24.102Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: output behavior tests passed including calendar output precedence."
  "2026-04-04T20:40:18.489Z",codex-agent,Reopened and reparented under pm-122q after duplicate scan; existing closed task already covered calendar output UX and is the canonical record to extend for agent/LLM deterministic parsing improvements.
  "2026-04-04T21:12:05.151Z",codex-agent,"Implemented calendar UX enhancements for agent/LLM consumption: richer summary aggregates (by_kind/by_type/by_status/recurring_events), deterministic markdown event metadata tokens, recurrence rendering details, and command-aware calendar highlight alignment. Added focused calendar tests for metadata/warnings/end-time formatting branches. Evidence: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test (69 files / 856 tests passed), node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed (branch 91.03%), and pm test-all --status in_progress passed linked calendar checks."
  "2026-04-06T23:08:02.487Z",codex-agent,"Reopened as canonical remediation tracker under pm-o7be for current audit findings wave to avoid duplicate item creation. Scope retained from prior implementation lineage and expanded for new report deltas only. Decision rationale: duplicate-check sweep in this run found no open/in-progress item directly covering this exact delta while this closed item already contains closest historical context, linked artifacts, and verification lineage."
  "2026-04-25T23:06:39.889Z",audit-agent,"Dogfood calendar audit evidence: views/day-week-month-agenda, include filters, recurrence windows, and validation errors all behaved deterministically. UX gap observed: --event recurrence multi-value fields require '|' delimiters inside a CSV entry; comma-separated weekday values currently trigger generic parse errors before recurrence-specific validation guidance."
  "2026-04-26T08:42:52.498Z",codex-agent,"Calendar dogfood evidence 2026-04-26: recurrence works when using event field recur_by_weekday with pipe-delimited weekdays (mon|tue|wed|thu|fri). Initial attempts with recur_byweekday or comma-separated weekday lists fail with generic invalid --event payload error. UX opportunity remains to surface an explicit recurrence field/delimiter hint in the parse error path for agent-oriented troubleshooting."
  "2026-04-26T13:16:13.798Z",cursor-agent,"Fresh calendar audit evidence 2026-04-26: valid day/week/month/agenda commands pass with --date now and ISO/from-to values, recurrence expansion works, and context includes agenda data. The audit checklist's --date today probe fails with invalid argument guidance; consider supporting today as an alias or documenting that agents must use now/relative/ISO values."
  "2026-04-26T13:51:52.747Z",cursor-agent,"Telemetry evidence from persisted user data analysis: calendar had 127 finishes and 14 failures for an 11.02 percent failure rate. Repeated failure pattern includes invalid --date value today with 5 occurrences, matching the existing calendar UX follow-up scope."
  "2026-04-26T14:51:49.698Z",audit-agent,"2026-04-26 audit confirms calendar works in all 4 views (agenda/day/week/month). Reminders and deadlines render correctly. Recurrence expansion verified. Outstanding: no local timezone support, no reminder recurrence, no iCal export, --limit is blunt global cap."
  "2026-04-26T19:56:59.875Z",codex-agent,"Phase 4A/4B/4C audit evidence: verified machine-parseable json and toon outputs in agenda/day/week/month views, renamed rendered row type from CalendarEvent to CalendarRow in calendar/context command surfaces, and validated recurring/event/deadline/reminder rendering through dogfood command matrix."
  "2026-04-26T19:57:02.431Z",codex-agent,"Verification evidence: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/calendar-command.spec.ts tests/unit/context-command.spec.ts (passes) and broader 12-file regression suite including calendar command pathways."
  "2026-04-26T19:57:04.569Z",codex-agent,"Outstanding follow-up retained in this item: better recurrence parse guidance and date alias ergonomics (for example today alias) remain open UX improvements beyond current acceptance checks."
  "2026-04-27T17:44:09.055Z",codex-agent,"Execution 2026-04-27: implemented calendar boundary support for --date/--from/--to value 'today' and added explicit recurrence delimiter guidance for malformed --event CSV entries. Verification: pm test pm-kglq --run --progress passed all linked suites (20 + 33 + 30 tests)."
